# ConversionOS

Landing Page Attribution & Payout Platform for a real estate agency.
Marketing profiles (social accounts) drive traffic to custom landing pages.
Form submissions become Bitrix24 leads; the system attributes each lead to a profile and calculates payouts.

## Stack

- Next.js 14 (App Router, TypeScript)
- Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage + Realtime)
- Puck (`@measured-co/puck`) for landing editing
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- pnpm · Vercel

## Architecture

- `/app/(dashboard)/` — Protected admin panel (auth required)
- `/app/l/[profile]/[landing]/` — Public landings (SSR, SEO)
- `/app/api/track/` — Server-side tracking (visit, lead)
- `/app/api/webhooks/bitrix/` — Bitrix24 outgoing webhook events
- `/app/api/leads/` — Lead submission and Bitrix sync
- `/lib/supabase/` — Supabase clients (server, client, admin)
- `/lib/bitrix/` — Bitrix24 API wrapper
- `/lib/puck/` — Puck config and custom blocks

## Core Entities

- **Profile** — Marketing account; `slug` in URLs; `commission_rate`
- **Landing** — Page at `/l/{profile_slug}/{landing_slug}`; Puck JSON blocks
- **Visit** — Pageview; `session_id`, referrer, device
- **Lead** — Form submit; `bitrix_lead_id`, optional `bitrix_deal_id`
- **Payout** — Per profile per period from converted leads × `deal_value` × `commission_rate`

## Key Business Rules

- Every visit to `/l/{profile}/{landing}` creates a Visit before render
- Every form submit creates a Lead AND calls Bitrix `crm.lead.add`
- Lead stores `session_id` (links Visit → Profile)
- On Bitrix `ONCRMDEALUPDATE` with stage WON: find Lead by `bitrix_lead_id`, mark converted
- Payout = `SUM(deal_value) × commission_rate` for converted leads in the period, per profile
